He that deals with Pitch must expect no
better, black will to black, quoth the Divel to the Collier;
but, dost thou think there is a Heaven or Hell?

I'le break that Custome, 'tis a rude one;
hast thou no wit Wench? canst thou pick out no better
title for me.

I profess thou art dull, abhominable dull;
dost thou not know upon what Score my dear, and secondself
is gon to Wallingford-House.

They were not bound to their good behaviour,
but—'Tis well they Understand their Duties;
set Us Our Chair of State, and then admit 'um.

